&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;At RES, we’re looking for purpose-driven individuals who are passionate about restoration and sustainability, and who want their work to make a lasting environmental impact. Our team members go above and beyond, bringing initiative, integrity, and a strong work ethic to every project. Collaboration is key—we thrive on teamwork, open communication, and diverse perspectives. In a field that constantly changes, we value those who are resilient, adaptable, and resourceful in the face of challenges. If you&#39;re intellectually curious, eager to learn, and ready to help restore ecosystems and protect natural resources, you’ll find your place here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We are looking for an EHS&amp;amp;S Specialist to join our team, in Lafayette, LA, covering LA, TX and FL regions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;581&quot; data-end=&quot;917&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The EHS&amp;amp;S Specialist will support RES operations throughout Louisiana, Texas, Florida, and other areas as assigned, ensuring environmental, health, safety, and security compliance across a wide variety of construction and ecological restoration projects. This role reflects RES’s commitment to our employees, clients, and communities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;919&quot; data-end=&quot;922&quot;&gt;
